To find the Cartesian product A x B, we form all possible ordered pairs with the first element from set A and the second element from set B. Similarly, we find the Cartesian product B x A by forming all possible ordered pairs with the first element from set B and the second element from set A. Then, we find the union of these two sets.

A x B = {(1, 3), (1, 4), (2, 3), (2, 4)}
B x A = {(3, 1), (3, 2), (4, 1), (4, 2)}

Now, we find the union of these two sets:

(A x B) ∪ (B x A) = {(1, 3), (1, 4), (2, 3), (2, 4), (3, 1), (3, 2), (4, 1), (4, 2)}
